We had already seen brief introduction about [using Query function](http://blogmines.com/blog/2011/08/29/how-to-use-query-function-in-google-spreadsheet/) in **Google Spreadsheet**. Let us see **how to limit the number of rows** returned using Query Function with the following sample data of batsman with maximum runs in test cricket.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Now if you want to get the top 3 batsman with maximum number of runs scored, then you can use

**\=QUERY(C3:G13,"selectC,Glimit3")**

The limit keyword will **reduce the number of results** returned to 3.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

But say if you want to get the list of top 3 batsman with maximum averages then need to use the Order by clause.

**\=QUERY(C3:G13,"selectC,ForderbyFdesclimit3")**

The above query would first sort the list using **Order by** clause and then uses the **limit** keyword to get the Top results.

![](data:image/png;base64,)
